name: pyperunner
raw_meta_yaml:
{% set name = "pyperunner" %}
{% set version = "0.1.2" %}

package:
  name: "{{ name|lower }}"
  version: "{{ version }}"

source:
  url: "https://pypi.io/packages/source/{{ name[0] }}/{{ name }}/{{ name }}-{{ version }}.tar.gz"
  sha256: beb73a64290beb5553cbc3bd1b128191658d8e94d7913fcf4e1e3edff88dfb03

build:
  noarch: python
  number: 0
  script: "{{ PYTHON }} -m pip install . -vv"

requirements:
  host:
    - python >=3.7
    - pip
  run:
    - coloredlogs >=15.0
    - gitpython >=3.1.12
    - grandalf >=0.6
    - joblib >=0.17.0
    - networkx >=2.5
    - pydot >=1.4.1
    - python >=3.7
    - pyyaml >=5.4.1

test:
  imports:
    - pyperunner
    - pyperunner.dag
    - pyperunner.environment
    - pyperunner.runner

about:
  home: "https://github.com/glichtner/pyperunner/"
  license: "GPL-3.0-only"
  license_file: LICENSE
  summary: "Yet another ETL pipeline runner for python, using multiprocessing and directed acyclic graphs."
  doc_url:  "https://pyperunner.readthedocs.io/"
  dev_url: "https://github.com/glichtner/pyperunner/"

extra:
  recipe-maintainers:
    - glichtner
